BT /F1 10 Tf 54 420.8 Td (  Total tax: ~$47,160) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 397.0 Td (With S-Corp election \(same $120K profit\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 383.0 Td (  Reasonable salary: $60,000 \(payroll taxes apply\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 369.0 Td (  Payroll taxes on salary \(15.3%\): $9,180) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 355.0 Td (  Distribution \(not subject to SE tax\): $60,000) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 341.0 Td (  Income tax on all $120K \(24%\): $28,800) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 327.0 Td (  Total tax: ~$37,980) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 303.2 Td (  TAX SAVINGS: $9,180 per year!) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 275.4 Td (REQUIREMENTS FOR S-CORP:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 259.4 Td (- Must pay yourself a 'reasonable salary' \(IRS watches this closely\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 245.4 Td (- Must run payroll \(use Gusto $40/mo or QuickBooks Payroll $45/mo\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 231.4 Td (- Must file Form 1120S annually \(separate corporate return\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 217.4 Td (- File Form 2553 with IRS to elect \(deadline: March 15 of tax year\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 189.6 Td (THE BREAK-EVEN POINT:) Tj ET
