BT /F1 10 Tf 54 686.0 Td (- Q2 \(Apr-May income\): Due June 15) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 672.0 Td (- Q3 \(Jun-Aug income\): Due September 15) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 658.0 Td (- Q4 \(Sep-Dec income\): Due January 15 \(following year\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 630.2 Td (HOW TO CALCULATE YOUR QUARTERLY PAYMENT:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (Method 1 - Simple \(Best for Year 1\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 600.2 Td (- Take last quarter's net profit) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 586.2 Td (- Multiply by 30% \(covers income tax + SE tax for most people\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 572.2 Td (- That's your quarterly payment amount) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 548.4 Td (Method 2 - Safe Harbor \(Best for Year 2+\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534.4 Td (- Pay 100% of LAST year's total tax liability, divided by 4) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 520.4 Td (- \(110% if your AGI was over $150,000\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 506.4 Td (- This guarantees zero underpayment penalties regardless of this year's income) Tj ET
