BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.2 Td (- End prices in 7 or 9 \($497, $997, $2,497\) for perceived value) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.2 Td (- Name your packages \(don't just say 'Basic/Standard/Premium'\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.2 Td (- Highlight the middle tier as 'Most Popular' or 'Best Value') Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 492.4 Td (Pricing Mistakes to Avoid) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 464.6 Td (- 1. PRICING BY THE HOUR when you should price by the project) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 450.6 Td (   \(Hourly pricing penalizes you for getting faster/better\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 426.8 Td (- 2. MATCHING THE CHEAPEST COMPETITOR) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 412.8 Td (   \(You can't compete on price and quality - choose quality\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 389.0 Td (- 3. GIVING DISCOUNTS instead of adding value) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 375.0 Td (   \(Add a bonus worth $X instead of cutting your price by $X\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 351.2 Td (- 4. NOT RAISING PRICES annually) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 337.2 Td (   \(Inflation alone means you earn less each year if prices stay flat\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 313.4 Td (- 5. LETTING CLIENTS SET YOUR PRICE) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299.4 Td (   \(Never ask 'what's your budget?' before presenting your rate\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 275.6 Td (- 6. UNDERVALUING because of imposter syndrome) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 261.6 Td (   \(You don't need 10 years experience to charge professional rates\)) Tj ET
endstream
